==Other fatalities== ===Team members=== At the 1975 [[Safari Rally]], a service car with four mechanics crashed into a truck near [[Mombasa]]. Carlino Dacista, Brian Fernandez and Willie Uis died instantly. The driver David Joshi sustained serious injuries.<ref>{{cite web | title=Carlino Dacista | work=Motorsport Memorial | url=http://www.motorsportmemorial.org/focus.php?db=ct&n=4095 | accessdate=18 September 2008}}</ref> At the 1978 [[Monte Carlo Rally]], two mechanics, Bernard Balmer and Georges Reinier, died when their van collided with a truck near [[Gap, Hautes-Alpes|Gap]], [[Hautes-Alpes]].<ref>{{cite web | title=Bernard Balmer | work=Motorsport Memorial | url=http://www.motorsportmemorial.org/focus.php?db=ct&n=6939 | accessdate=18 September 2008}}</ref> On the second day of the 1987 [[Rallye Côte d'Ivoire]], [[Toyota Team Europe]]'s [[Cessna 340]] crashed and exploded, killing all four inside; manager and former co-driver [[Henry Liddon (driver)|Henry Liddon]], his assistant Nigel Harris, the pilot and the navigator. Team manager [[Ove Andersson]] withdrew Toyota from the event. Prior to the accident, [[Björn Waldegård]] and [[Fred Gallagher (co-driver)|Fred Gallagher]] had been running second in their [[Toyota Supra in motorsport|Toyota Supra Turbo]].<ref>{{cite web | title=Henry Liddon | work=Motorsport Memorial | url=http://www.motorsportmemorial.org/focus.php?db=ct&n=5847 | accessdate=18 September 2008}}</ref> At the 1996 [[Safari Rally]], competed in bad weather and rain, three British mechanics drowned while attempting to cross a river with their [[Land Rover]].<ref>{{cite web | title=1996 Safari Rally | work=Motorsport Memorial | url=http://www.motorsportmemorial.org/focus.php?db=ct&q=a&n=6052 | accessdate=18 September 2008}}</ref>
===Officials=== At the end of the fourth stage of the 1981 [[1000 Lakes Rally]], [[Audi Sport]] driver [[Franz Wittmann, Sr.|Franz Wittmann]] and his co-driver Kurt Nestinger did not notice the flying finish which marks the end of the stage. They continued at race speed with their [[Audi Quattro|Quattro]] and crashed into a group of people standing in front of a van. Raul Falin, chairman of [[AKK-Motorsport|AKK]], Finland's sporting authority for motorsport and the country's representative in the FIA, was quickly taken to a hospital but died from his injuries soon after. Boris Rung, co-founder and chairman of the European Rallycross Association and member of FIA's Off-Road Commission, survived the accident along with Greek FIA observer Costas Glossotis.<ref>{{cite web | title=Raul Falin | work=Motorsport Memorial | url=http://www.motorsportmemorial.org/focus.php?db=ct&n=2387 | accessdate=18 September 2008}}</ref>
===Spectators=== At the 1978 Safari Rally, five passers-by and four spectators were killed in unrelated accidents, both involving non-competitive drivers crashing into competitors.<ref>{{cite web | title=1978 Safari Rally | work=Motorsport Memorial | url=http://www.motorsportmemorial.org/focus.php?db=ct&n=5350 | accessdate=18 September 2008}}</ref>
On the first stage of the 1986 [[Rally Portugal]], [[Joaquim Santos]] lost control of his [[Ford RS200]] while trying to avoid spectators on the road, crashing into a crowd of spectators, killing three and injuring over thirty.<ref>{{cite journal | journal=[[St. Petersburg Times]] | title=3 Portuguese spectators killed by skidding racer | pages=29 | date=6 March 1986 | url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=X-EMAAAAIBAJ&sjid=RGYDAAAAIBAJ&pg=5652,5698183}}</ref> All the factory teams &ndash; [[Audi]], [[Austin Rover]], [[Ford]], [[Lancia]], [[Peugeot]] and [[Volkswagen]] &ndash; withdrew from the event.<ref>{{cite web | title=20º Rallye de Portugal Vinho do Porto | work=RallyBase | url=http://www.rallybase.nl/index.php?type=result&rallyid=217 | accessdate=18 September 2008}}</ref>
At the 1996 1000 Lakes Rally, at a special stage that took place in the centre of [[Jyväskylä]], one spectator died and 36 were injured when [[Danish people|Danish]] driver [[Karsten Richardt]] lost control of his [[Mitsubishi Lancer Evolution]]. Rikhard reached the curve at {{convert|120|kph|mph}}, finally hitting the crowd at {{convert|40|kph|mph}}.<ref>{{cite web | title=Katsojaonnettomuus Jyväskylän Suurajoissa 23.8.1996 | url=http://www.onnettomuustutkinta.fi/uploads/oqj4l9uk1tmx6rr.pdf | accessdate=20 July 2009}}</ref>
At the 2017 Monte Carlo Rally, a spectator died after [[Hayden Paddon]] slid wide on a left-hand corner and went rear-first on the roadside embankment.<ref>{{cite web | title=Spectator dies after Monte Carlo WRC crash | url=http://www.motorsport.com/wrc/news/spectator-dies-after-monte-carlo-wrc-crash-866998/ | accessdate=20 January 2017}}</ref>
